// E2E tests for `Workspace newClass: source at: path` (ADR 0082 Phase 1, BT-2285).
//
// `newClass:at:` compiles and installs a brand-new class in memory and logs a
// durable `kind: "new-class"` ChangeEntry. Phase 1 does NOT write the file to
// disk (that is Phase 2 flush). It must raise a loud, specific error — no silent
// fallback — for each of the four validation cases (ADR 0082, *`Workspace
// newClass:` validation*).
//
// These cases require E2E because the live FFI path runs only in a running
// workspace. The shared E2E session has no project (`project_path` undefined),
// so every candidate path classifies as "outside the project source tree". That
// makes two validation rules deterministic here and lets us assert them against
// the live workspace:
//   (a) target already exists on disk  — checked first, fires for any file;
//   (b) target outside the project tree — fires for any non-existing path,
//       because with no project context there is no tree to create the file in.
// The name-mismatch (c) and already-loaded (d) rules are shadowed by (b) in this
// project-less session; their pure validation logic is covered deterministically
// by the loader's EUnit tests (declared_class_name/1, validate_new_class/3), and
// the new-class ChangeEntry shape by the changelog gen_server's EUnit tests.

// Workspace responds to #newClass:at: (FFI dispatch wired)
Workspace respondsTo: #newClass:at:
// => true

// ===========================================================================
// (a) TARGET ALREADY EXISTS ON DISK
// ===========================================================================

// An existing fixture file is a loud error — checked before any project context,
// so it fires regardless of whether a project is loaded.
Workspace newClass: "Object subclass: Counter" at: "tests/repl-protocol/fixtures/counter.bt"
// => ERROR: already exists

// ===========================================================================
// (b) TARGET OUTSIDE THE PROJECT SOURCE TREE
// ===========================================================================

// A path that does not exist and is not inside the current project tree is a
// loud error. In this project-less session every non-existing path qualifies.
Workspace newClass: "Object subclass: Greeter" at: "/nonexistent/elsewhere/greeter.bt"
// => ERROR: outside the project source tree

// ===========================================================================
// TYPE ERRORS — both arguments must be Strings
// ===========================================================================

// Non-String source is a loud type error, not a silent fallback.
Workspace newClass: 42 at: "src/greeter.bt"
// => ERROR: expects a String source

// Non-String path is a loud type error.
Workspace newClass: "Object subclass: Greeter" at: 42
// => ERROR: expects a String path
